I will agree on some of your views about the Bible, most of it is very outdated, yet i grew up with it, and I have my reasons for not agreeing with it, instead of just outright flaming it.  Do you really know what &quot;turn the other cheek means?&quot;  or &quot;it is easier for a camel to pass through the eye of the needle, than for a rich man to go to heaven&quot; means?  If you do then I'll shut up right now because your talking about your dislike of the religion/bible from experience, and not just an outsiders view of it.  Oh, and neither of those quotes are anywhere close to what most people think they mean today.<br>
